{
  "text": "Such skepticism is shared in ongoing research about the kinds of personal attributes about which people can report reliably in a survey (see, e.g., Tourangeau, et. al. 2000: Chapters 3, 6, and 11.3) and work on how conventional survey interviewing techniques sometimes produces atypical and unrepresentative responses [CITATION_1] .",
